<br>
You can feign apathy all you want, but all people have feelings. Just because you don't care if someone makes fun of you based on an attribute of your person that is beyond your control, doesn't mean that that entitles you to degrade other people for the same reasons. This is not a &quot;stupid&quot; issue, as so many of you vehemently proclaim. This debate is questioning whether or not it is right to use offensive words if you don't intend them to upset the audiences the represent. The general consensus here is &quot;you're gay, go to hell if you disagree with me.&quot;<br>
<br>
Lasgalen, as a homosexual, has a right to be upset if some moron throws around &quot;gay&quot; while playing it off as meaning &quot;dumb.&quot; Doing this is drawing a comparison between homosexuality and dumbness, which is an insult to homosexuals. It's calling all gay people dumb. This is the same as calling all minorities poor. It doesn't matter if your intent is just using the lingo you were taught yesterday by your fourth grade buddies, it's how it is perceived that matters.<br>
<br>
The bottom line: if you are insulted, you have a right to respond. This right is just as strong as the freedom of speech. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ualyissa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alyissa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/2/02 12:42:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting offended</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If someone wants to call me cracker ass motherfucker whitey it honestly wouldn't bother me.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
