<br>
IF it were anyone on the board getting bent about the usage of the word gay other than Lasgalen, I think everyone would have said 'YEAH, BE NICE' and this would have been done with.<br>
<br>
Combine in some Observation:<br>
<br>
I'm 32 and I've used the term for BOTH things on and off for two, maybe two and a half decades.<br>
<br>
Is it insensitive? yeah, probably. I'm sorry, but you pick up a LOT of bad habits being surrounded by more adolescents than adults all day.<br>
<br>
Do I have anything against people based on what they do in bed or what kind of person they fall in love with? Not a chance, you should do the holidays with my family.<br>
<br>
Do I think this is a straight-gay issue? Nope.<br>
<br>
I think this is a tolerance issue on BOTH sides of the fence. I think that what this is... is 2 groups of people, neither of them even close to a majority of the population,  who have a silly stake in the issue of this one fucking word.<br>
<br>
SOLUTION - READ ON -<br>
<br>
Retire the word 'gay'<br>
<br>
Strike it from our language.<br>
<br>
All of the people who used it to describe their lifestyle get to pick a NEW WORD to describe their lifestyle.<br>
<br>
All of the people who used it as a derogatory get to pick a NEW WORD that is DIFFERENT from the above word to make fun of people, etc. with.<br>
<br>
All of the people who used it to describe happiness need to GO THE FUCK BACK TO 1890.<br>
<br>
Caveats: the aggrieved get to pick first.<br>
No one can pick the word 'Todd,' it would just be too fucking wierd.<br>
<br>
